      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.mGD4IPKZN4ruO73T]{Evolutionary Focus}</p>\n<p>You wield your adaptive strike intuitively, raining blows upon your enemies.</p>\n<p><strong>@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.SD7998OEKJe5cJU7]{Basic}:</strong> When making a full attack you take a –3 penalty to attacks made with your adaptive strike instead of the normal –4 penalty.</p>\n<p><strong>@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.sa0ffr80j4FIXRb6]{Advanced (13th Level)}:</strong> When making a full attack entirely with your adaptive strike, you can make three attacks instead of two attacks. You take a –5 penalty to these attacks instead of a –3 penalty.</p>\n<p><strong>@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.KR4YcDKBvV0hWbcH]{Ultimate (19th Level)}:</strong> Once per round when you make a full attack and hit the same target at least twice with your adaptive strike, you can exaggerate the target’s wounds (such as by rending them, creating a deadly current, or triggering secondary explosions), dealing 5d10 additional damage (Fortitude half).</p>"
